OL,5,ETHE GREEN CROSS TOAD        R    "/m|t+
OL,7,BWildlife workers count the toads which 
OL,8,Buse theEspecial underpass,Bnote their  
OL,9,Bsex and then release them.             
OL,11,BMales usually head up the migration,   
OL,12,Bwith the larger females following. On  
OL,13,Breaching the ponds, the males then     
OL,14,Eclasp the females,Bwho can carry them  
OL,15,Bfor several weeks.                     
OL,16,B                                       
OL,17,BOnce the females have finished spawning
OL,18,BtheyEreturn across the road,Bthe males 
OL,19,Bfollowing on when they have all crossed
